<SECOND>PM-BRF--Paraguay-Minister,0121</SECOND>
<HEAD>Defense Minister Resigns</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ASUNCION, Paraguay (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Army Gen. Adolfo Samaniego has
resigned as national defense minister, President Gen. Andres
Rodriguez announced.
   Rodriguez gave no reason for the resignation, which he disclosed
to reporters at the national palace on Friday.
   Rodriguez ousted former President Gen. Alfredo Stroessner in a
coup Feb. 3 and was elected president in May.
   Samaniego, 65, served as ambassador to Brazil under Stroessner.
A replacement was not immediately named.
</TEXT>
