<HEAD>No. 2 HUD Official to Decide Fate of Troubled Housing Agency</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The No. 2 official at the Department of
Housing and Urban Development says he'll ask Cleveland-area
officials to shake up the management of their housing authority.
   But HUD Undersecretary Al Dellibovi opposes a federal takeover
of the long-troubled agency.
   ``The problem is basically a management problem and I think
clearly the management in place is not up to the challenge at
hand,'' Dellibovi said Friday about the Cuyahoga Metropolitan
Housing Authority. ``The solution to this kind of local problem is
not a federal takeover.''
