<FIRST>r a PM-People-Springsteen     08-12 0164</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-People-Springsteen,0168</SECOND>
<HEAD>The Boss Takes Stage With Ringo in New Jersey</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HOLMDEL, N.J. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Rock star Bruce Springsteen, watching Ringo
Starr and his band at a performance, gave the audience a treat by
jumping on stage and playing alongside the former Beatles drummer.
   Springsteen, who made his name playing small venues on the
Jersey shore, joined Starr on Friday at the Garden State Arts
Center for the concert's final four songs, beginning with the
Beatles classic ``Get Back.''
   Starr is on a 30-city U.S. tour which began in Dallas on July 23
and closes in Los Angeles on Sept. 4. Among those accompanying him
are two members of Springsteen's E Street Band, saxophonist
Clarence Clemens and guitarist Nils Lofgren.
   Springsteen joined the band in ``Have Some Fun Tonight,''
Starr's early solo hit ``Photograph,'' and the finale, the Beatles'
``With A Little Help From My Friends.''
   Also joining the band for the finale was comedian John Candy,
who clowned and played the tambourine.
