<FIRST>r i PM-BRF--Sweden-Soviet     08-12 0105</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-BRF--Sweden-Soviet,0107</SECOND>
<HEAD>Soviet Official Expelled</HEAD>
<DATELINE>STOCKHOLM, Sweden (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An official posted at the Soviet
general consulate in Gothenburg has been expelled for alleged
industrial espionage, according to the Swedish Foreign Ministry.
   The official, who has already left Sweden, is accused of trying
to obtain classified information about Swedish and foreign
technology, Foreign Ministry sources said Friday.
   The ministry announced the expulsion on Friday but declined to
say when the official left the country. A statement issued by the
ministry did not mention whether the Soviet official had diplomatic
status.
   According to ministry sources and Swedish media, the nation's
security interests were not damaged.
</TEXT>
