<FILEID>AP-NR-08-12-89 0848EDT</FILEID>
<FIRST>r i PM-Israel     08-12 0423</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Israel,0435</SECOND>
<HEAD>Two Suspected Collaborators Killed in West Bank</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By MARJORIE OLSTER</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>JERUSALEM (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Masked Palestinians today killed two Arabs
suspected of collaborating with Israeli authorities in the West
Bank, stabbing one and hanging the other in a school courtyard,
Arab reports said.
   In southern Lebanon, Israeli troops and allied Lebanese
militiamen Thursday night shot and wounded a guerrilla whose unit
planned to infiltrate Israel, the army said. The wounded man was
captured, but his companions escaped.
   In the Askar refugee camp near Nablus, masked Palestinians
repeatedly stabbed Murshed Kaniery, 55, after accusing him of
collaborating with Israeli security forces, Arab reports said. He
died later in a Nablus hospital.
   In Bidiya village near Tulkarem in the West Bank, masked Arabs
hanged 30-year-old school teacher Jamal Taha in his school's
courtyard, Arabs said.
   Palestinians said the army imposed a curfew on Bidiya after the
early-morning killing and deployed hundreds of troops to search the
village and surrounding fields for the attackers.
   The deaths raised to at least 94 the number of Palestinians
killed by fellow Arabs during the 20-month-old uprising against
Israeli rule, most of them on suspicion of collaborating with
Israel.
   Troops or Jewish settlers have killed 534 Palestinians during
the uprising. Thirty-eight Jews have also been killed.
   Israeli soldiers detected the guerrilla squad near Markaba
village in the central sector of Israel's self-declared security
zone, an army statement said.
   The force opened fire, wounding one guerilla who was captured by
South Lebanese Army militiamen allied with Israel, the statement
said. The rest of the squad escaped. None of the Israel or militia
troops was injured.
   The statement said the squad apparently planned to carry out an
attack on a northern Israeli settlement, but it gave no details.
   Israel radio said Israeli and militia units conducted widespread
searches for the other guerrillas and quoted a senior army officer
as saying they apparently were Palestinians.
   The clash occurred 1.5 miles from the Israeli settlement of
Misgav Am near the Lebanese border. It was the third incident in
the security zone this month.
   On Wednesday, five Israeli soldiers were wounded, one of them
critically, when a suicide bomber from the Moslem fundamentalist
Hezbollah militia drove an explosive-laden car into an Israeli
convoy two miles north of the Israeli border near Qleiaa village. A
militiaman also was wounded in the blast.
   On Aug. 1, militiamen shot and killed three guerillas from the
Popular Front for the Liberation of Palestine in the central sector
of the security zone near Hula village.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
