<FIRST>r i AM-BRF--ShipFire     08-12 0146</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--Ship Fire,0148</SECOND>
<HEAD>Ship Catches Fire in Greek Harbor, Passengers Evacuated</HEAD>
<DATELINE>RHODES, Greece (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A fire broke out aboard a cruise ship
after it collided with a pier while docking Saturday, but all 45
passengers were evacuated safely, harbor authorities said.
   The ship developed engine trouble when it tried to dock in heavy
winds, a harbor official on this Aegean island said.
   The wind pushed the 1,500-ton Zeus II against one of the piers,
cracking its stern. Minutes later, a fire broke out in the engine
room.
   The fire was quickly extinguished, and there was no significant
damage to the engine room, said the harbor official in a telephone
interview.
   The passengers, mostly Belgian, Dutch and German, were ``quickly
and safely evacuated,'' said the official. Harbor authorities were
inspecting the damage to see whether the ship could continue its
cruise of the Dodecanese islands.
</TEXT>
