<HEAD>Four Standing Under Tree Injured in Lightning Strike</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ANN ARBOR, Mich. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Four soccer players seeking shelter
under a tree during a thunderstorm were injured when lightning
struck, police said.
   The storm hit Thursday night during a game in an adult soccer
league, police Sgt. Jack Ceo said.
   Kyle Wertz, 30, and Stephane Titart, 28, both of Ann Arbor,
remained in critical condition Friday at the University of Michigan
Medical Center, officials there said.
   Andrew Irving, 19, of Dexter was in good condition at St. Joseph
Mercy Hospital. Kyle Baker, also 19, of Ypsilanti, was treated and
released.
   The lightning strike knocked down several other players who
didn't require hospitalization, Ceo said.
</TEXT>
